[[Image:<U+2022>Big Spring, TX sign IMG 1438.JPG|200px|right|thumb|Big Spring decorative sign]]

[[Image:"Big Spring" of Big Spring, TX IMG 1430.JPG|200px|right|thumb|The "big spring" in Comanche Trail Park in Big Spring, Texas]]

'''Big Spring''' is a city in and the [[county seat]] of [[Howard County, Texas|Howard County]], [[Texas]], [[United States]], at the crossroads of [[U.S. Highway 87]] and [[Interstate 20]].  With a population of 27,291 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], it is the largest city between [[Midland, Texas|Midland]] to the west, [[Abilene, Texas|Abilene]] to the east, [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock]] to the north, and [[San Angelo, Texas|San Angelo]] to the south. Big Spring was established as the county seat of Howard County in 1882; it is the largest community in the county.

The city got its name from the single, large spring that issued into a small gorge between the base of Scenic Mountain and a neighboring hill in the southwestern part of the city limits.  Although the name is sometimes still mistakenly pluralized, it is officially singular. "To the native or established residents who may wince at the plural in Big Springs, it should be explained that until about 1916, when for some unexplained reason the name dropped the final "s," the official name of the town was indeed Big Springs." <ref>{{cite book|last=Pickle|first=Joe|title=Gettin' started, Howard County's first 25 years|year=1980|publisher=Heritage Museum|location=Big Springs [sic], Tex.|isbn=0-89015-268-3}}</ref> There is also a small community named [[Big Springs, Texas]], located in [[Rusk County, Texas|Rusk County]] in [[East Texas]].

==Geography==
Big Spring is located at {{Coord|32|14|36|N|101|28|31|W|type:city}} (32.243198, -101.475231).<ref name="GR1">{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/gazette.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>

According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|19.2|sqmi|km2}}. About {{convert|19.1|sqmi|km2}} of it is land, and {{convert|0.1|sqmi|km2}} of it (0.42%) is covered with water.

